
@startuml

' Define classes
class Hospital {
    - id: String
    - name: String
}

class ExaminationType {
    - code: String
    - name: String
    - description: String
}

class Permission {
    - hospital_id: String
    - examination_type_code: String
    - granted_at: Date
}

class Problem {
    - id: String
    - name: String
    - description: String
}

class TreatmentPlan {
    - problem_id: String
    - advised_examination_type_code: String
    - sequence_order: Integer
}

class Doctor {
    - id: String
    - name: String
    - affiliated_hospital_id: String
}

class Patient {
    - id: String
    - name: String
}

class Diagnosis {
    - patient_id: String
    - doctor_id: String
    - problem_id: String
    - diagnosed_at: Date
}

class ActualTreatment {
    - diagnosis_id: String
    - treatment_plan_id: String?
    - notes: String
}

class MedicalAction {
    - actual_treatment_id: String
    - type: String
    - details: String
}

class Examination {
    - medical_action_id: String
    - examination_type_code: String
    - performed_at_hospital_id: String
    - scheduled_for: Date
    - performed_at: Date
}

' Relationships
Hospital "1" -- "0..*" Permission : has permission for
ExaminationType "1" -- "0..*" Permission : can be given to
Hospital "1" -- "0..*" Diagnosis : serves patients at
Doctor "1" -- "1" Hospital : affiliated with
Problem "1" -- "1..*" TreatmentPlan : has treatment plan for
TreatmentPlan "1" -- "1" ExaminationType : includes
Diagnosis "1" -- "1" ActualTreatment : leads to
ActualTreatment "1" -- "0..*" MedicalAction : includes
MedicalAction "1" -- "0..1" Examination : may be an examination
MedicalAction "1" -- "0..1" OtherAction : may be other action (e.g., medication)
Examination "1" -- "1" Hospital : performed at

' Notes for clarity
note right of Permission
  A hospital can apply for permission
  to perform specific types of examinations.
end note

note right of ActualTreatment
  Can deviate from the standard treatment plan.
  May include both advised and freely chosen actions.
end note

note right of Examination
  An examination must be performed at a hospital 
  that has permission for that type.
end note

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Hospital**: Represents a healthcare facility.
- **ExaminationType**: Describes the type of examination (e.g., NMR scan).
- **Permission**: Links hospitals to allowed examination types.
- **Problem**: A medical issue for which a treatment plan exists.
- **TreatmentPlan**: A standardized set of recommended examinations for a problem.
- **Doctor**: A medical professional affiliated with a hospital.
- **Patient**: The individual receiving care.
- **Diagnosis**: A doctor's assessment of a patient’s problem.
- **ActualTreatment**: The real treatment applied to a patient, possibly differing from the treatment plan.
- **MedicalAction**: Any action taken as part of the treatment—could be an examination or something else.
- **Examination**: A specific instance of a medical test, linked to a type and a hospital.

